Package planet

Class Planet

  • java.lang.Object
    • planet.Planet
  • public class Planet
extends java.lang.Object
    Represents planets that may exist in a GameEnvironment instance. The name is chosen from an array of name Strings. One Transporter part may be found per planet.
    Author:
    mch221

      • searchPlanet

        public java.lang.Object searchPlanet​(CrewMember crewSearcher,
                                     java.util.List<FoodItem> foodItems,
                                     java.util.List<MedicalItem> medicalItems,
                                     Crew currentCrew)
        Allows crew members to search a planet. There is an equal chance of finding a FoodItem, MedicalItem, money, nothing, or, if no transporter part has yet been found on the current Planet, a transporter part. Scientist class crew members have a higher chance of finding transporter parts.
        Parameters:
        crewSearcher - takes a CrewMember object to conduct the search.
        foodItems - takes a List of FoodItem objects that may be found on the planet.
        medicalItems - takes a List of MedicalItem objects that may be found on the planet.
        currentCrew - takes the current instance of Crew to allow found items to be added to the inventory.
        Returns:
        the object found, if any, while searching the planet.
